      ],
      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Aptos,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">A pathologist receives a lung biopsy from a 38-year-old man with suspected fungal pneumonia. Which stain would be most appropriate to use first to identify potential fungal elements within the tissue?</span></span></span></span></p>",
