      "text": "<p style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\"><span style=\"font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif\">In a patient with a disseminated fungal infection, a bronchoalveolar lavage is performed. The cytopathology team observes oval yeast cells within macrophages. Which staining method is correctly matched with the fungal organism likely to be visualized with this presentation?</span></span></p>",
      "unique_key": "Q2706941",
      "question_audio": null,
      "question_video": null,
      "map_id": 35686,
      "difficulty_level": "intermediate",
